[0.005, "o", "\u001b[36mв•ӯв”Җ\u001b[0m\u001b[36mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\u001b[0m\u001b[36m answer (tight) \u001b[0m\u001b[36mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\u001b[0m\u001b[36mв”Җв•®\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m The LLM router picks a provider for a given tier by calling the        \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36;40m_provider\u001b[0m method in the \u001b[1;36;40mModelRouter\u001b[0m class, which in turn calls the     \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36;40mprovider_for\u001b[0m method of the \u001b[1;36;40mProfile\u001b[0m class. Specifically, the process is \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m as follows:                                                            \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m                                                                        \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0mThe \u001b[1;36;40mModelRouter._provider\u001b[0m method is invoked with the specified      \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mtier, which calls \u001b[1;36;40mself._active.provider_for(tier)\u001b[0m                   \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0m(packages/asil_core/asil_core/llm/router.py:77).                    \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0mThe \u001b[1;36;40mProfile.provider_for\u001b[0m method retrieves the provider from the     \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mchat\u001b[0m dictionary using the tier as the key                           \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0m(packages/asil_core/asil_core/llm/profiles.py:40).                  \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m                                                                        \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m If the tier does not exist in the \u001b[1;36;40mchat\u001b[0m dictionary, a \u001b[1;36;40mValueError\u001b[0m is     \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m raised (packages/asil_core/asil_core/llm/profiles.py:40).              \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m                                                                        \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m Additional evidence regarding how the \u001b[1;36;40mProfile\u001b[0m is initialized and what  \u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36mв”Ӯ\u001b[0m providers are availab"]
